				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hrmm I must be entirely lacking the ability to state my suggestion in a format that is understood.  Here is a summary.
<br />

<br />
Bad Changes: 30 minute duration; 15 minute reuse - requires another hotkey.  
<br />

<br />
Indifferent: Group & MGB & AE spells still hit pet like they do now with absolutely zero changes.
<br />

<br />
Good Change: Ability to effectively "zone" your pet into instanced or other pre-buff areas where your pet gets blessed with the same group buffs you are wearing upon activation.  Identical down to the time remaining on the buffs.
<br />

<br />
I can see it being a nerf for the raiders who typically chain pet after pet on mobs that eat them via AE, rampage or otherwise faster than 15 minutes per.  This is hypothetical on my behalf as I assume such situations must exist somewhere for somebody.  How detrimental would this really be in these situations?  Even with PoC & MS4's rune?
<br />

<br />
Discuss why you would be opposed to this - please fill me in.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=501504">Anthe Battlecaster</a>
